csare\", \"from\": 8497, \"to\": 8517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While WADA was invited to send a representative to the hearing, the agency declined.\", \"from\": 8564, \"to\": 8648, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 8570, \"to\": 8574}, {\"ngram\": \"a representative\", \"from\": 8595, \"to\": 8611}, {\"ngram\": \"the hearing\", \"from\": 8615, \"to\": 8626}, {\"ngram\": \"the agency\", \"from\": 8628, \"to\": 8638}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA considers it inappropriate to be pulled into a political debate before a U.S. congressional committee regarding a case from a different country, especially while an independent review into WADA's handling of the case is ongoing,\\\" the organization said Tuesdayin a statement.\", \"from\": 8650, \"to\": 8930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8729, \"end\": 8757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_congressional_committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"U.S. congressional committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_congressional_committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_congressional_committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 8651, \"to\": 8655}, {\"ngram\": \"a political debate\", \"from\": 8701, \"to\": 8719}, {\"ngram\": \"a case\", \"from\": 8768, \"to\": 8774}, {\"ngram\": \"a different country\", \"from\": 8780, \"to\": 8799}, {\"ngram\": \"an independent review\", \"from\": 8818, \"to\": 8839}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's handling\", \"from\": 8845, \"to\": 8860}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 8864, \"to\": 8872}, {\"ngram\": \"the organization\", \"from\": 8886, \"to\": 8902}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesdayin\", \"from\": 8908, \"to\": 8917}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As WADA expected, today's congressional hearing focused on pushing out more misinformation regarding the contamination case from 2021 involving 23 swimmers from China, and causing further damage to WADA's reputation and that of the global anti-doping system,\\\" said WADA President Witold Ba\\u0144ka.\", \"from\": 8932, \"to\": 9226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9094, \"end\": 9099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999818536412308, \"rank\": 1.7281267934509248e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 9213, \"end\": 9219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"score\": 0.9999999974402272, \"rank\": 2.5599286209009878e-09, \"text\": \"Witold\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 8936, \"to\": 8940}, {\"ngram\": \"today's congressional hearing\", \"from\": 8951, \"to\": 8980}, {\"ngram\": \"more misinformation\", \"from\": 9004, \"to\": 9023}, {\"ngram\": \"the contamination case\", \"from\": 9034, \"to\": 9056}, {\"ngram\": \"23 swimmers\", \"from\": 9077, \"to\": 9088}, {\"ngram\": \"further damage\", \"from\": 9113, \"to\": 9127}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA's reputation\", \"from\": 9131, \"to\": 9148}, {\"ngram\": \"the global anti-doping system\", \"from\": 9161, \"to\": 9190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is not appropriate for anti-doping to be politicized in this way.\", \"from\": 9228, \"to\": 9297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this way\", \"from\": 9288, \"to\": 9296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All it does is weaken confidence in the system, which ultimately does not benefit athletes from the United States or anywhere else,\\\" Ba\\u0144ka added.\", \"from\": 9298, \"to\": 9443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9398, \"end\": 9411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.999951892509996, \"rank\": 4.81098044948655e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http